Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Cementos Lima, Siderperu, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-05T17:49:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/peru-stocks-buenaventura-cementos-lima-siderperu-volcan.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:17 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima  General Index rose 0.5 percent to 21,275.12. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index gained 1 percent to 2,910.95.  Industrial stocks gained as investors bought shares that
had fallen to “attractive levels,” BBVA Banco Continental
chief analyst Miguel Leiva said in a telephone interview.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., rose 1.5 percent to 3.50 soles. The shares
fell 19 percent this year through yesterday.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1) 
(CEMLIMC1 PE), the country’s biggest cement maker, climbed 1.4
percent to 37.50 soles after plunging 24 percent this year
through yesterday.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1
PE), a unit of Gerdau SA, Latin America’s largest steelmaker,
gained 1.3 percent to 1.58 soles. The shares dropped 22 percent
this year through yesterday.  Miners gained after metals rebounded in New York and
 London .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, rose 1.9 percent to $43.21.
 Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer,
gained 1.5 percent to $40.60. Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1
PE), Peru’s largest silver producer, rose 1.1 percent to 3.85
soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  